# Single Handler Pattern

**When to apply:** Use when rendering a list of items (e.g. `.map()`) where each item needs an `onClick` or similar handler that passes an item-specific value. One handler + `data-*` avoids N allocations per render.

**Problem:** `onClick={() => handlePlay(c.key)}` per item creates N new functions per render.

**Solution:** One handler + `data-*` attribute. Read the key from the event target.

**Pattern:**
```tsx
const handleCardClick = useCallback((e: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => {
  const key = e.currentTarget.dataset.cardKey
  if (key) handlePlayRef.current(key)
}, [])

<button data-card-key={c.key} onClick={handleCardClick}>...</button>
```

**Example:** [frontend/src/App.tsx](frontend/src/App.tsx) – `handleCardClick` + `data-card-key` for card grid and in-hand slots.

**Reduces:** Allocations per render (N → 1); helps GC when parent re-renders often.
